 "redflags": [
  "Two load-bearing quantitative claims (94% leave-one-out accuracy and permutation p=4e-4 on N=17; STRING network density 0.35 vs 0.67) are asserted but not independently verifiable from the text, and N=17 with class sizes ~9 vs 8 is small enough that the held-out-accuracy statistic is fragile despite the reported robustness checks.",
  "C2/C3 mortality kinetics are explicitly acknowledged as assuming an exponential individual hazard rather than deriving it, and were never fit to primary life tables (SSA data not accessed) \u2014 the Gompertz law and late-life plateau are shown only as sufficiency/generic-frailty effects, not derivations, so these constraints support the hypothesis more weakly than the framework's presentation might suggest.",
  "The central discriminating prediction cannot separate open-loop drift from hyperfunction (the author concedes it is a 'sibling'), so even a successful pilot leaves the hypothesis observationally equivalent to a well-established prior theory on its own decisive test.",
  "The 'blind re-coding by an independent classifier' that reproduced labels 16/17 is described but its independence cannot be checked here; the same author-controlled mechanism-direction coding is the load-bearing step of the only 'predicts' empirical test.",
  "Output-contract conflict: the kernel profile requested plausibility/reasoning_trace axes while the user turn's STRICT CONTRACT requested grounding/reasoning/completeness/usefulness/creativity -- I followed the explicit trailing contract but note the two are inconsistent.",
  "C5 evidential weight is overstated relative to its base: N=17 compounds, mechanism coding is the load-bearing step, and 94% leave-one-out accuracy on N=17 is fragile; the blind re-classification and aspirin-robustness checks mitigate but the permutation p-values should be read as suggestive, not decisive.",
  "The headline claim 'youthful function is recoverable by restoring the regulatory input alone -- damage and the epigenetic clock left untouched' is presented in the bottom-line summary as an established prediction of the theory, but the body correctly concedes it is UNTESTED and does not discriminate from hyperfunction; the summary reads more confidently than the honest-limits section warrants.",
  "Several constraint fits (C2, C3) are explicitly 'sufficiency, not derivation' and the Gompertz kinetics are simulated by ASSUMING exponential individual hazard -- the model demonstrates consistency, not that drift generates the law, which slightly undercuts the 'one premise generates the Gompertz curve' framing in the bottom line."
 ],
